# Git Commit Rules for Gacharoo

## Format

Every commit message follows Conventional Commits:

```
type(scope): concise description in imperative mood
```

Optional body (separated by blank line):
```
type(scope): concise description

Why this change was made. Not what -- the diff shows what.
```

## Type (required)

- `feat` -- New feature or capability
- `fix` -- Bug fix
- `refactor` -- Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
- `perf` -- Performance improvement
- `style` -- Formatting, missing semicolons, etc (no code logic change)
- `docs` -- Documentation only
- `test` -- Adding or updating tests
- `chore` -- Build process, tooling, dependencies, CI
- `a11y` -- Accessibility improvement
- `i18n` -- Internationalization / translation

## Scope (required)

Use the feature domain:

`cards` `packs` `battle` `trading` `import` `collection` `social` `ads` `auth` `db` `infra` `a11y` `i18n` `ui`

Multiple scopes: use the primary one. If truly cross-cutting, omit scope: `refactor: extract shared card types`

## Subject Line Rules

- Max 72 characters
- Imperative mood: "add" not "added", "fix" not "fixes"
- Lowercase after the colon: `feat(cards): add holographic shader` not `Add Holographic Shader`
- No trailing period
- Be specific: `fix(packs): prevent duplicate card in same pack` not `fix(packs): fix bug`

## Body Rules (optional, use for non-obvious changes)

- Separated from subject by a blank line
- Explains WHY, not WHAT
- Wrap at 80 characters
- Use bullet points with `-` for lists
- Reference issue numbers: `Closes #42`

## What Makes a Good vs Bad Commit Message

Good:
```
feat(packs): implement server-side RNG with rarity weights

- 60/20/20 pool split for normal/golden/trade-only cards
- Soft pity halves drop weight after 3x duplicate pulls
- Adaptive pack size based on set card count
```

```
fix(cards): prevent near-miss teasing in rarity reveal UI
```

```
perf(battle): pre-compute ghost snapshots on team save
```

```
a11y(cards): add rarity symbols for colorblind double-coding
```

Bad:
```
Update files                          # too vague
Fixed the thing                       # not informative
feat: Added a new feature for cards   # past tense, no scope, redundant
WIP                                   # never commit WIP
feat(packs): This commit adds the ability to open packs with a new animation
                                      # too long, not imperative
```

## Commit Granularity

- One logical change per commit
- Prefer many small commits over one giant commit
- If a change touches multiple features, consider splitting into separate commits
- Database migrations get their own commit: `chore(db): add user_wishlists table`
- Dependency changes get their own commit: `chore: add react-spring and @react-three/drei`

## Avoid

- Never commit `.env` files, secrets, or API keys
- Never commit `node_modules/`, `.next/`, `data/` directories
- Never commit `bun.lockb` changes without corresponding `package.json` changes
- Never use `--no-verify` to skip hooks
- Never force push to main
